Nigerian Disc Jockey DJ Expression has opined that music is one of the notable things uniting Africa. The fascinating disc jockey held that African musicians are doing incredibly well in putting the continent in the positive spotlight despite all the negative stories people in the diaspora read about Africa. DJ Expression further added that the unrelenting habit and the fighting spirit African musicians possess is part of why music from the continent has dominated the globe.   Seven Nigerian celebrities with honorary doctorate degrees     Davido congratulates Adeleke for receiving certificate of…     Apostle Chibuzor withdraws Aguba’s marriage gifts, transfers…   “Hardly will you get to any part of the world and not listen to African songs, and the moment these songs play, you will see Africans dancing and showing love to one another.” “The drive and fighting spirit that African musicians have is quite applaudable. They are not stopping; this is why the entire world is now paying attention to our songs,” he added in a chat with entertainment reporter. DJ Expression, who has become a household name in America and Africa, further stipulated that “there are a lot of negative stories about Africa on the international media, but for entertainment, especially music, the news is always palatable and positive.”